Sentencas: X-ray diffraction was used to determine phase of nanocrystalline Ce1 2xGdxLaxO delta and Ce1 2xGdxNdxO delta (x = 0.1, 0.25).

Sentencas: Conduction mechanism (dc conductivity and ac conductivity) in prepared samples was observed as a function of temperature and frequency.

Sentencas: DC conductivity was measured in temperature range 300-700 degrees C. AC conductivity was measured in frequency range 1 kHz to 3 MHz at temperatures 300, 400, 500, 600, and 700 degrees C.

Sentencas: The enhancement in conductivity was observed due to availability of oxygen vacancy sites which was dependent on composition.

Sentencas: The Raman measurements supported the electrical conductivity results and more vacancy sites were observed in Raman spectrum in samples which showed maximum conductivities.
Titulo: Temperature and frequency dependence of transport phenomena in co-doped rare earth oxides nanoparticles for ITSOFCs

Sentencas: The maximum conductivity achieved was 1.78 S cm (1) (at 600 degrees C) for Ce0.5Gd0.25Nd0.25O delta, which is quite a higher value in these compounds.
Titulo: Temperature and frequency dependence of transport phenomena in co-doped rare earth oxides nanoparticles for ITSOFCs
